text.tspan: Share of adult women overweight or obese vs. daily caloric supply, 2013 to
The share of adult women defined as overweight or obese, measured as the percentage of women with a body mass index
(BMI) greater than 25, versus the daily caloric supply, measured in kilocalories per person per day. BMI is a person's weight (in
kilograms) divided by their height (in meters) squared.
Share of women overweight or obese
Source: Prevalence of weight categories in females - NCDRisC (2017), Our World in Data based on UN FAO & historical sources
